# Custom Theme System — T3 Code

## Context

The app already has a light/dark/system mode toggle (`apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts`) that
toggles the `.dark` class on `<html>` and reads Tailwind's `@variant dark` CSS rules.
The task adds a **named colour-palette system** ("t3-dark", "t3-light", "t3-midnight") on
top of that infrastructure. Each named theme ships its own background, foreground, accent,
sidebar, editor, terminal, and status-bar colours. Selecting a theme persists the choice to
localStorage, applies CSS custom properties directly via `element.style.setProperty()`
(inline-style precedence beats `:root` and `@variant dark` rules), and toggles `.dark`
appropriately. A `ThemeProvider` context + `useColorTheme` hook expose the selection to the
React tree; a new `ThemeSelector` component renders preview swatches in the Settings page.

**Constraint:** no new dependencies; no build-config changes.

---

## Critical Files

| File | Action |
|---|---|
| `packages/shared/src/theme.ts` | **Create** — theme types + 3 built-in definitions |
| `packages/shared/package.json` | **Modify** — add `./theme` subpath export |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeProvider.tsx` | **Create** — context provider + `useColorTheme` hook |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` | **Create** — swatch UI component |
| `apps/web/src/index.css` | **Modify** — declare default `--theme-*` fallback vars in `:root` |
| `apps/web/src/router.ts` | **Modify** — wrap children with `ThemeProvider` |
| `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` | **Modify** — add `ThemeSelector` to Appearance section |

---

